definition: tree/wood/coffin/wooden/simple/numb/one of the eight categories of ancient musical instruments 八音[ba1 yin1]

sentences.english: The planet Jupiter blazes near the waxing gibbous moon tonight.
sentences.chinese: 今晚光辉四溢的木星和月亮拉近了距离。

sentences.english: Ben:"Since Mercury10 has crossed paths with Jupiter, your fortunes are falling."
sentences.chinese: 墨丘利神已经穿过木星的轨道，你的运气正在下落。

sentences.english: Our sky chart shows the bright waxing gibbous moon and the planet Jupiter for around mid-evening tonight.
sentences.chinese: 今日的星图展示了午夜前后明亮的凸月和木星。

sentences.english: Mars, this week, edges slowly closer towards a right-angle with Jupiter.
sentences.chinese: 火星本周缓缓移近与木星成直角的位置。

sentences.english: On those days Mercury will conjoin Jupiter, a lovely influence.
sentences.chinese: 届时水星将结合木星，产生可爱的影响力。

sentences.english: That’s Jupiter doing its cosmic job, astronomers like to say.
sentences.chinese: 天文学家说啊，木星在太空上班，这是它分内的事。

sentences.english: Recent Jovian impact probably came from a giant meteorite.
sentences.chinese: 最近木星陨撃可能来自一巨大流星体。

sentences.english: Lucky Jupiter plants itself in compatible Earth sign Taurus for an entire year.
sentences.chinese: 幸运的木星位于土象的金牛座并持续一整年。

sentences.english: Metis and Adrastea lie within Jupiter's main ring.
sentences.chinese: 木卫十六与木卫十五存在于木星主光环之内。

sentences.english: The probe was the first to sample the atmosphere of a gas planet.
sentences.chinese: 该探测器第一次在木星这个气体行星的大气层里采样。

sentences.english: With Mercury squaring up to Neptune and Jupiter we're talking about high hopes.
sentences.chinese: 因为水星与海王星和木星成方角的意思就是的厚望。

sentences.english: An Ancient Storm in the Jovian Atmosphere.
sentences.chinese: 大红斑是木星大气层中一个古老的风暴。

sentences.english: Juno’s principal goal is to understand the origin and evolution of Jupiter.
sentences.chinese: 朱诺的首要目标是了解木星的起源和进化。

sentences.english: Jupiter also darts into Aries mid-year, tripling the mental energy.
sentences.chinese: 木星也会在年中时期撞入白羊，使精神能量臻至三倍。

sentences.english: Village life DuanMuXing tracking cloud reactive son.
sentences.chinese: 中村功命端木星跟踪云子。

sentences.english: Uranus (surprise) and Jupiter (generosity and expansion) will both be outstandingly supportive.
sentences.chinese: 天王星和木星也将会给于大力的支持。

definition: Vesta, an asteroid, second most massive object in the asteroid belt between Mars and Jupiter, discovered in 1807 by H.W. Olbers
